The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	Bengal captain Laxmi Ratan Shukla relinquished the Kalighat captaincy Saturday to focus more on state captaincy and the upcoming Indian Premier League matches for Kolkata Knight Riders. His Bengal team deputy Manoj Tiwary will lead Kalighat for the remainder of the season.       
	I want to relax a bit while playing club cricket. Captaining a premier club side like Kalighat and Bengal was putting a bit of pressure on me. My immediate focus is the Vijay Hazare Trophy and then IPL, Shukla said.           
	 Wriddhiman Saha, who has been selected in the Indian team for the first Test against South Africa, scored an unbeaten 82 as Mohun Bagan beat Ballygunge United by eight wickets in a CAB league match Saturday.      
